1
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:09,767
<i>The footage was looped,
so we can't track them down.</i>

2
00:00:09,767 --> 00:00:10,900
<i> This is the area.</i>

3
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:12,467
<i>This is where
they brought Father.</i>

4
00:00:12,467 --> 00:00:13,867
<i> I can't be wrong.</i>

5
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:17,033
What's the motive of the people
<i> who took your father?</i>

6
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:18,667
<i>I don't know!
All I know is,</i>

7
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:20,100
<i>the longer Father
remains missing,</i>

8
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:21,633
<i> the more danger he'll be in.</i>

9
00:00:21,633 --> 00:00:24,400
[GRUNTING]

10
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:25,400
[LOUD CRASH]

11
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:26,467
[PHONE BEEPING]

12
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:28,067
<i> He's still there. Step on it.</i>

13
00:00:28,067 --> 00:00:29,100
<i> Yes, ma'am.</i>

14
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:31,100
[GLASS BREAKING]

15
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:33,733
[GRUNTING]

16
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,000
<i> You?!</i>

17
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:39,300
<i> Son of a...</i>

18
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:44,300
<i>- Wait, you might hit Marcus.
- What the hell?!</i>

19
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:49,100
[GUNSHOTS]

20
00:00:49,167 --> 00:00:50,167
<i> Felix!</i>

21
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,033
<i>- That's enough!
- Gun down!</i>

22
00:00:53,033 --> 00:00:54,100
<i> We need him alive.</i>

23
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:56,100
<i> He's getting away!</i>

24
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:57,133
<i> Jalil! Let's go!</i>

25
00:00:58,167 --> 00:00:59,767
<i>Forensics,
this is Agent Angeles.</i>

26
00:00:59,767 --> 00:01:01,467
<i>I need a
facial composite, urgent.</i>

27
00:01:01,633 --> 00:01:02,767
<i> Who's that guy?</i>

28
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:06,400
<i>I first saw him on the island
when we arrested Datu Rahman.</i>

29
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:09,467
I saw him again when Datu Rahman
<i> was taken from the streets.</i>

30
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,167
<i>He was supposed
to let Datu Rahman escape,</i>

31
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:12,667
<i>but the kidnappers
got to him first?</i>

32
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:14,933
<i>We need to find him
to find out the truth.</i>

33
00:01:15,233 --> 00:01:16,300
<i> I need you to find someone.</i>

34
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,667
Let's take him to the hospital!

35
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,200
<i> I trust you, Jamilah.</i>

36
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,500
<i> Not the hospital.</i>

37
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:22,700
<i> Bring him to the house.</i>

38
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,833
<i>- And keep quiet.
- We will.</i>

39
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:26,800
<i> I'll hide the car out back.</i>

40
00:01:27,033 --> 00:01:28,467
Let's proceed to Barangay Surga.

41
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:30,000
<i> The Muslim community?</i>

42
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:44,700
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:57,367
[SIRENS WAILING]

44
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:08,367
[NORHANA] Omar, has the doctor
picked up yet?

45
00:02:08,367 --> 00:02:09,367
Not yet.

46
00:02:09,367 --> 00:02:13,633
- [NORHANA] Omar, Jalil...
- [JAMILAH CRYING]

47
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,367
Agent Angeles, this is
what I came up with

48
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:18,167
- based on the descriptors.
- Thank you.

49
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,700
Marcus, can you check
if it's accurate?

50
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:28,600
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [OFFICERS TALKING ON RADIO]

51
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,400
[GRUNTING]

52
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:36,833
[GRUNTING]

53
00:02:41,233 --> 00:02:42,267
Circulate.

54
00:02:42,267 --> 00:02:43,500
Copy, Agent Angeles.

55
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:50,600
All units, listen up.

56
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:52,733
The suspect is an
unidentified male.

57
00:02:52,733 --> 00:02:54,433
Study the facial composite.

58
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:55,733
Memorize the face.

59
00:02:57,267 --> 00:02:59,833
Also, the subject has
a gunshot wound to the side.

60
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:01,567
Approach with caution.

61
00:03:03,467 --> 00:03:04,600
Understood?

62
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,767
- Roger, ma'am.
- Roger, ma'am.

63
00:03:05,767 --> 00:03:06,867
Alright, let's go.

64
00:03:19,267 --> 00:03:24,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

65
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:26,133
We mean you no harm.

66
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:29,167
We're here because
we're looking for a suspect.

67
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:32,333
Do you know this man?

68
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:43,433
If you have any information
on his whereabouts,

69
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:45,600
please let us know immediately.

70
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,767
We're only here
to ask questions.

71
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:52,300
Nothing bad will happen
if you cooperate.

72
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:58,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

73
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:00,467
- Omar!
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]

74
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:03,700
- [MAN] Mister Omar!
- Open it.

75
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:05,833
The police are almost here!

76
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:08,467
- Okay, thank you.
- [NORHANA] What do we do?

77
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,533
Sir.

78
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:13,833
Does this man
look familiar to you?

79
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:18,167
No, I don't know him.

80
00:04:18,733 --> 00:04:22,167
Okay. Ask around.

81
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,367
Keep your eyes peeled.

82
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:26,800
Hey.

83
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,633
Have you seen this man?

84
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:31,867
Is he a celebrity?

85
00:04:32,067 --> 00:04:34,533
I'm not kidding.
Are you hiding him?

86
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:37,233
I don't know him, sir.

87
00:04:39,733 --> 00:04:40,833
Okay.

88
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,633
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

89
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:44,700
Follow me.

90
00:04:46,067 --> 00:04:47,833
Do you know this man?

91
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:50,800
We don't know him.

92
00:04:52,267 --> 00:04:53,333
Thank you.

93
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:56,333
(In Maranao) I'm sorry.

94
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:57,367
[SIGHS]

95
00:04:57,367 --> 00:05:00,800
Seriously, Usman?
Why did you bring them here?

96
00:05:02,633 --> 00:05:04,633
- We're looking for--
- You're a Muslim too.

97
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:07,233
You know it's strictly forbidden
for us to harbor criminals.

98
00:05:08,033 --> 00:05:09,300
I'm sorry.

99
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:16,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

100
00:05:25,967 --> 00:05:27,433
Do you know this man?

101
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:30,600
I don't know him.

102
00:05:32,733 --> 00:05:33,733
Okay, thank you.

103
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:43,700
No.

104
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:47,967
Good evening, ma'am.

105
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:50,533
Does this man
look familiar to you?

106
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:52,967
I'm busy.

107
00:05:52,967 --> 00:05:59,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

108
00:05:59,767 --> 00:06:02,767
Who can we speak to here?
Do you have a barangay captain?

109
00:06:02,967 --> 00:06:04,800
Yes. Omar.
His house is over there.

110
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:06,800
- Over there?
- [WOMAN] Yes.

111
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,967
Thank you.

112
00:06:10,667 --> 00:06:13,300
- [JAMILAH] Help us carry him.
- Help them.

113
00:06:13,467 --> 00:06:15,533
[NORHANA] Jalil... Jalil...
Hang in there, Jalil.

114
00:06:15,533 --> 00:06:17,467
This way. Follow me.

115
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:18,433
[NORHANA] Jalil...

116
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:21,100
- [NORHANA] Careful.
- Let's go.

117
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:23,867
[OMAR] Come on, hurry.

118
00:06:23,867 --> 00:06:25,133
Let's go.

119
00:06:25,133 --> 00:06:26,100
[GRUNTS]

120
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:33,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

121
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:35,333
[NORHANA] Jalil...

122
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,600
[NORHANA WHIMPERING]

123
00:06:50,367 --> 00:06:57,133
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [PANICKED BREATHING]

124
00:06:59,633 --> 00:07:02,067
[NADIA] There, look!

125
00:07:02,067 --> 00:07:04,967
They're raiding us even though
we haven't done anything wrong!

126
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:11,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

127
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:19,533
[WHIMPERING, PANTING]

128
00:07:20,933 --> 00:07:22,867
Oh no... [WHIMPERS]

129
00:07:28,067 --> 00:07:35,000
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WHIMPERING]

130
00:07:51,767 --> 00:07:58,233
[SOBBING]

131
00:07:58,233 --> 00:08:00,133
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

132
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:01,700
Aah! [GRUNTS]

133
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:05,567
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

134
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:06,933
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

135
00:08:13,233 --> 00:08:15,833
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]
- [WHIMPERS] Wait!

136
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:24,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

137
00:08:24,067 --> 00:08:25,767
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

138
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:28,033
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

139
00:08:32,967 --> 00:08:34,067
I'm coming!

140
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,167
Who's there?

141
00:08:37,167 --> 00:08:42,000
[TENSE MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

142
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,900
- Who-- Oh!
- [BOTTLE SHATTERS]

143
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,100
Goodness!

144
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:47,133
You startled me! Move aside!

145
00:08:47,267 --> 00:08:49,300
I said, move!

146
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,033
[NORHANA] Ouch.

147
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:58,500
You were banging on my door
like some maniac!

148
00:09:00,267 --> 00:09:01,600
Who are you?

149
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:03,233
Is Omar here?

150
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,933
Why are you looking
for my husband?

151
00:09:05,933 --> 00:09:07,100
He's not here.

152
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:09,033
We just want to ask if--

153
00:09:09,033 --> 00:09:10,967
Do you know this criminal?

154
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,133
Take a good look.

155
00:09:13,133 --> 00:09:16,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,233
Look closely!

157
00:09:20,033 --> 00:09:21,933
[FELIX] I know you're
hiding him here.

158
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:30,833
[FELIX] Look!

159
00:09:31,867 --> 00:09:34,967
There's no criminal here.

160
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,900
Look--

161
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:38,200
I'm sorry.

162
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:42,100
[NORHANA] Yeah, right.
Now I have to clean this up.

163
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,167
Scram!

164
00:09:47,867 --> 00:09:48,967
Let's check that one.

165
00:09:48,967 --> 00:09:52,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

166
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:53,833
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

167
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:58,000
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

168
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:04,067
[FELIX] Let's check
the other side.

169
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:11,967
Let's go.

170
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:27,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:10:29,867 --> 00:10:31,333
[SIGHS IN RELIEF]

172
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:36,700
[SIGHS IN RELIEF SHAKILY]

173
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:37,867
[LINE RINGING]

174
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:40,767
Doc! Doc, please pick up!

175
00:10:42,733 --> 00:10:44,367
- Doc--
- Jalil!

176
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:47,267
- [JALIL WHIMPERS]
- Hang in there.

177
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:48,767
[JALIL GRUNTS]

178
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:52,967
[JALIL GRUNTING IN PAIN]

179
00:10:52,967 --> 00:10:54,033
[OMAR] Hurry.

180
00:10:54,033 --> 00:11:00,233
[JALIL BREATHING LABORIOUSLY]

181
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:07,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

182
00:11:10,933 --> 00:11:12,100
Reyes?

183
00:11:13,667 --> 00:11:15,100
Goddammit.

184
00:11:18,233 --> 00:11:19,767
[LINE RINGS]

185
00:11:19,767 --> 00:11:21,233
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

186
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,733
[HUFFS] Hello?

187
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:24,700
<i>- Yes, sir?
- Angeles!</i>

188
00:11:25,967 --> 00:11:28,933
What is Reyes doing there, huh?!

189
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:31,233
<i> He's supposed to be suspended!</i>

190
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,867
Sir, Agent Reyes is not here
as an agent.

191
00:11:33,933 --> 00:11:36,300
He's here to
identify the target.

192
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:37,867
<i> Angeles!</i>

193
00:11:37,967 --> 00:11:40,633
You and Reyes sure are full of--

194
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:41,400
<i> Respectfully, sir,</i>

195
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:43,467
I would really love to hear
everything you have to say,

196
00:11:43,467 --> 00:11:44,933
but now is not a good time.

197
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:46,233
Suit yourselves!

198
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,300
Just make sure...

199
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:52,267
<i>...that you'll catch
your target!</i>

200
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:59,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

201
00:11:59,133 --> 00:12:00,167
Let's go.

202
00:12:04,767 --> 00:12:06,000
Here. This way!

203
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:10,300
[JALIL BREATHING LABORIOUSLY]

204
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:12,100
Over here. Faster!

205
00:12:12,167 --> 00:12:17,967
[JALIL GRUNTING, WHEEZING]

206
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,200
- Mister Omar!
- It's a dead end.

207
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:27,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

208
00:12:29,233 --> 00:12:30,867
Did you find any leads?

209
00:12:30,867 --> 00:12:32,867
- No. How about you?
- No.

210
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:37,600
Damn it.

211
00:12:38,533 --> 00:12:40,433
Command,
negative on the visuals.

212
00:12:41,467 --> 00:12:42,867
No lead on suspect.

213
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:44,000
[RADIO CRACKLES]

214
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:52,067
Marcus, let's go.

215
00:12:52,067 --> 00:12:59,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

216
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:11,967
They're gone.

217
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:14,167
All clear?

218
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:26,533
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

219
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:31,100
Miss Norhana,
you can calm down now.

220
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,267
They're gone.

221
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:46,400
I'll head back to headquarters,
Ma'am Lara, Sir Marcus.

222
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,900
Okay, be safe.

223
00:13:52,067 --> 00:13:53,767
[FELIX CHUCKLING]

224
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:58,433
Your informant sucks.

225
00:13:59,167 --> 00:14:01,933
Can you not piss me off
right now, Domingo?

226
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:03,933
[LAUGHS]

227
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:07,067
I'll head back, too, Marcus.
I still need to file a report.

228
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,067
Lara.

229
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:11,900
What?

230
00:14:16,267 --> 00:14:18,067
Earlier, at the warehouse...

231
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:21,267
How did you know
where to find me?

232
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:24,867
You? It wasn't you
I was looking for.

233
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,933
An informant told me that
I might catch Datu Rahman there.

234
00:14:27,967 --> 00:14:29,333
That's why I was
at the warehouse.

235
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:36,467
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

236
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,300
Are we good, Reyes?

237
00:14:45,967 --> 00:14:47,267
I have to go.

238
00:14:47,267 --> 00:14:54,100
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:10,767
<i> Why are you monitoring me?</i>

240
00:15:14,167 --> 00:15:16,500
[JAMILAH] Uncle Omar,
she's not picking up!

241
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,333
[CRIES]

242
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,633
Just keep trying!

243
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:23,133
Maybe she's just busy
or she can't hear her phone.

244
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:25,867
- Just keep trying!
- She finally picked up!

245
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:26,967
Thank goodness.

246
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:30,367
H-Hello? Doctor?

247
00:15:31,133 --> 00:15:34,833
I need your help.
My nephew got shot.

248
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:39,667
Ah, yes. O-Okay.
We're near your house.

249
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:41,600
Oh, thank you, Doctor!

250
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:44,100
[CRYING CONTINUES]

251
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,633
Alright.

252
00:15:49,367 --> 00:15:53,167
The police are gone.
Omar is safe now.

253
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,567
I hope you're right.

254
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:57,567
But...

255
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:03,067
They won't stop
until they find Jalil.

256
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:05,567
Miss Norhana, don't worry.

257
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:09,667
Thank you so much
for your help.

258
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:13,933
Remember, Miss Norhana,
we're always here to help, okay?

259
00:16:17,633 --> 00:16:22,067
[JAMILAH SOBBING]

260
00:16:22,067 --> 00:16:23,533
Jalil, we're here.

261
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,933
Let's go!

262
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:33,733
[GRUNTING]

263
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:36,233
- Let's go.
- A-Ah...

264
00:16:36,233 --> 00:16:39,133
[JALIL GRUNTING IN PAIN]

265
00:16:39,133 --> 00:16:41,200
Hey, don't worry!

266
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,233
- Huh?
- My friends here are very nice.

267
00:16:43,433 --> 00:16:45,300
It's better to be safe.

268
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:46,467
[JALIL GRUNTS]

269
00:16:46,467 --> 00:16:48,100
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

270
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,233
[JAMILAH] Anyone home?

271
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:54,233
[JALIL WHEEZING]

272
00:16:55,567 --> 00:16:57,967
[TENSE STING]

273
00:16:58,267 --> 00:16:59,900
D-Doctor.

274
00:17:03,167 --> 00:17:04,633
Come in. Hurry.

275
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:06,600
Jamilah, go.

276
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:08,267
Come on, Jalil.

277
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:10,500
[JALIL WHEEZING]

278
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,400
- Come on!
- This way! Quick!

279
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,633
Careful now.

280
00:17:13,933 --> 00:17:15,100
Jalil...

281
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:18,467
Over here. Come on.

282
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:19,933
Put him on the bed.

283
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:21,500
- Come on.
- Jalil...

284
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:26,167
[GRUNTING]

285
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:32,167
- [JALIL WHEEZING]
- [CLOTH RIPPING]

286
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:35,467
I hope the bullet
didn't hit any vital organs.

287
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:38,333
- Wait. Let me check.
- Jalil, hang in there!

288
00:17:39,367 --> 00:17:44,200
- [JALIL WHIMPERING IN PAIN]
- [BLOOD, FLESH SQUELCHING]

289
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,467
It seems the bullet was lodged
in the muscular layer

290
00:17:46,467 --> 00:17:48,600
so a minor surgical removal
is needed

291
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:50,333
to prevent complications.

292
00:17:50,467 --> 00:17:52,467
Do what must be done, Doc.

293
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:57,033
- [FLESH, BLOOD SQUELCHING]
- [JALIL WHEEZING]

294
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,400
[BOTH YELL]

295
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:07,567
[GUNSHOT]

296
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:10,700
[BOTH GRUNTING]

297
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,200
<i> Hey!</i>

298
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:21,033
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:27,067
[GRUNTS]

300
00:18:32,433 --> 00:18:34,367
- [GUNSHOTS]
<i> - Felix! Enough!</i>

301
00:18:34,367 --> 00:18:36,333
[LARA] Stand down! Stand down!

302
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:39,333
<i> Someone helped him escape.</i>

303
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:44,367
<i>Who are you?
I must find you.</i>

304
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,100
What's your name?

305
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:55,467
- Hey.
- [JALIL GROANS]

306
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,200
What's your name?

307
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,867
Can you hear me?

308
00:19:00,133 --> 00:19:01,400
- Hey.
- [WEAKLY] Jalil...

309
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,300
Jalil? Okay, Jalil.

310
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:05,867
Um, don't fall asleep, okay?

311
00:19:08,267 --> 00:19:09,567
[JALIL WHEEZES]

312
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,433
Jalil, just hang in there.

313
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:13,200
[JALIL CONTINUES WHEEZING]

314
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,400
What's his blood type?

315
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,833
AB negative, Doc.

316
00:19:17,133 --> 00:19:19,833
Good thing he and my son
have the same blood type.

317
00:19:23,767 --> 00:19:26,200
[JALIL WHEEZING, GROANING]

318
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:27,600
[JAMILAH] Jalil...

319
00:19:30,267 --> 00:19:33,267
- I'll start the surgery.
- [CELLPHONE RINGS]

320
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:36,300
[RINGING CONTINUES]

321
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:41,267
[LINE RINGING]

322
00:19:47,267 --> 00:19:50,100
Good thing Doc let us come here.

323
00:19:50,467 --> 00:19:52,133
<i> She's very kind.</i>

324
00:19:52,133 --> 00:19:54,933
<i>Sadly, one of her children
died early.</i>

325
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:58,500
<i> - Damn you. I'll make you pay.
</i>- [BLOWS LANDING]

326
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:00,433
- [GRUNTS]
- [SCREAMS IN ANGER]

327
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:05,733
<i> Can you give me a tour
</i>so I can meet my new neighbors?

328
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:08,300
<i> That Reyes is so stubborn!</i>

329
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:09,467
<i> And you're tolerating him!</i>

330
00:20:09,633 --> 00:20:12,833
All I'm saying is suspending him
<i> was the wrong move.</i>

331
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,467
<i> We'll solve this case faster</i>

332
00:20:15,467 --> 00:20:17,733
<i>if you let Agent Reyes
back on duty.</i>

333
00:20:17,933 --> 00:20:21,600
<i> Those who took Datu Rahman
</i>are part of a larger syndicate.

334
00:20:21,767 --> 00:20:24,700
<i>And they're using
the smuggled firearms</i>

335
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:26,767
<i>that we've been trying
to track down.</i>

336
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,900
[GRUNTING]

337
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:32,667
<i> Who are you?</i>

338
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:35,100
<i> I must find you.</i>

339
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:37,467
<i> I'm on my way home, Ma.</i>

340
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:41,300
<i>He's the one who took Father.
He's hunting down Jalil.</i>

341
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:43,167
<i> We've got to go.</i>

342
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:45,333
<i> I'm already at the gate
of our subdivision.</i>

343
00:20:45,567 --> 00:20:47,667
<i>- We have to go, Doc.
- Jalil, let's go.</i>

344
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:51,333
<i>Hurry!
He'll be here any minute!</i>

345
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:56,667
[JALIL GROANING]

346
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:59,367
<i>Hurry, Jalil.
He might catch us here.</i>
